fxmlgui

Class GUICard

  • java.lang.Object
    • fxmlgui.GUICard

  • public class GUICard
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used as a controller for the Cards seen in the GUI. It does not care about anything else, but it has methods so that other classes that know about this card can see if any actions have been preformed on it.
    Author:
    William Elliman

    • Method Detail

      • setCard

        public void setCard(Card c,
                    boolean isDouble)
        Sets the GUI part of this card to match the card give. It will set the top and bottom texts to the artist and the center to the auction type.
        Parameters:
        c - the card that the GUI will try to match.
        isDouble - if this card is the one being auctioned, this will determine if an extra "x2" will be added to the center text.
